text_blocks.snippet: To your family members, you should commit to communication, emotional support, and spending quality time together. This includes actively listening, offering encouragement, and being present for important events. Additionally, make sure to help with household tasks, show affection, and celebrate their successes, no matter how small.
snippet_highlighted_words: communication, emotional support, and spending quality time together

list.title: Communication:
list.snippet: Be open and honest with your family members. Share your thoughts and feelings, and actively listen to theirs.

list.title: Emotional Support:
list.snippet: Be there for them during tough times, offer encouragement, and celebrate their achievements.

list.title: Quality Time:
list.snippet: Make an effort to spend time together, whether it's through planned activities or spontaneous moments. Put away your phone and be present.

list.title: Help Around the House:
list.snippet: Pitch in with chores and tasks to show that you're a team player and that you value their contributions.

list.title: Show Affection:
list.snippet: Verbalize your love and appreciation, and don't be afraid to show physical affection.

list.title: Celebrate Successes:
list.snippet: Acknowledge and celebrate your family members' accomplishments, no matter how big or small.

list.title: Be Reliable:
list.snippet: Follow through on your commitments and be someone they can always count on.

list.title: Respect Boundaries:
list.snippet: Recognize and respect each other's individual needs and boundaries.
